<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<title>HTML5 Semantic Elements</title>

<style>
body{
    font-family: Arial;
    margin:20px;
}

header{
    background-color: lightblue;
    padding:15px;
    text-align:center;
}

section{
    background-color: lightgray;
    padding:15px;
    margin-top:10px;
}

article{
    background-color: white;
    padding:15px;
    margin-top:10px;
    border:1px solid black;
}

footer{
    background-color: lightblue;
    text-align:center;
    padding:10px;
    margin-top:10px;
}
</style>

</head>

<body>

<header>
<h1>HTML5 Semantic Elements</h1>
<p>Study of HTML5 document structure</p>
</header>

<section>
<h2>About HTML5</h2>
<p>HTML5 is the latest version of HTML used to create modern web pages.</p>
</section>

<article>
<h2>Use of Semantic Elements</h2>
<p>Semantic elements clearly describe their meaning in a webpage.</p>
<p>Examples are header, section, article and footer.</p>
</article>

<footer>
<p>Created for HTML5 Practical</p>
</footer>

</body>
</html>